@node "INTRO" "Introduction to mEGA-vIEW FAME Version"

@{b}@{u}INTRODUCTION@{uu}@{ub}

In the year 1993 I've started using a BBS (Amiex V2.20) and most of the utils
available in these days won't fit my requirements, so I've decided to program
my own utils. One of the most important things I've coded was mEGA-vIEW for 
/X. It became one of the best viewers available. After FAME was introduced in
1996 it became more and more important to adapt mEGA-vIEW to FAME, as FAME has
much more options and possibilities Amiex won't ever have. After another year
my users have found some bugs I couldn't fix in the latest Release of 
mEGA-vIEW V2.15, so I decided to stop the development of the Amiex version and
began to write a complete new Version, which is now finished. It has much more
features like V2.15 and is 100% FAME-native. The main usage of mEGA-vIEW hasn't
changed compared to the Amiex Version, but some new commands are integrated to
make the whole thing a bit better ;)

@{u}Here'a a list of features of mEGA-vIEW V3.4:@{uu}

 - Support for: EXE,ZIP,LHA,LZX,DMS,ARJ,ZOO,ZOOM,WARP,SHRINK,AGUIDE,ICONS,RAR,
   TGZ,HTML,MP3

 - Allows to integrate other @{b}external utils@{ub} for additional filetypes

 - Unknown Filetypes could be viewed in @{b}HEX Mode@{ub}. 

 - Uses @{b}FileID.library V8+@{ub} to identify more than @{b}600@{ub} different Filetypes

 - Easy to configure (via @{b}Textfile(s)@{ub}, no Tooltypes anymore!)

 - Viewing supports now @{b}up-/down scrolling@{ub} via CRSR-Keys

 - Highly-optimized and could be loaded @{b}resident@{ub}

 - Better support for LHA/LZX/ZIP archives

 - Uses now an own directory to store temporary files. This directory will
   be removed as soon as mEGA-vIEW will be exited. No more forgotten files
   on your RAM: disks ;)

 - Allows to choose files via ASL requester when a local connect is detected 

@endnode

@node "REQUIREMENTS" "What you need to use mEGA-vIEW V3.4"

@{b}@{u}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}@{uu}

mEGA-vIEW is able to operate without any other utility installed, however if
you run it without any other tool you won't get any further support for 
archives etc. mEGA-vIEW itself is only able to show plain textfiles and
hexviews of unknown files. The real strength will be shown if you use external
programs. 

Here's a list of things which are @{u}IMPORTANT@{uu}, as mEGA-vIEW won't work without 
them:

 - FAME BBS V1.3x running (Make sure that you have at least V1.30 !)

 - Amiga OS V3.x (lower won't work anymore, as it uses now memory pools!)

 - PIPE: Device mounted (standard when installing Workbench V3.x)

 - FileID.library V8+ installed (lower versions won't work!)


And these programs are directly supported by mEGA-vIEW:

    UnArj V2.41                                     DMS V2.04
    CheckExe V1.0ß                                  LHA V1.50
    LZX V1.21 (lower Versions WON'T WORK!)          UnZIP V5.31
    @{b}Guide2DocProf V0.3@{ub}                              Shrink V1.1
    WarpCk V1.4                                     ZoomChk V0.1
    Zoo V2.1                                        DMSDescript V1.1
    EXEDescript V1.0                                @{b}HTMLess V3.0@{ub}
    UnRAR V2.0                                      @{b}UnTar V1.5@{ub}

Note that programs written in BOLD are included in the release of mEGA-vIEW.

It is of course possible that other versions of the listed programs will work,
too. The list should only give you an overview for which programs I've tested
mEGA-vIEW.
@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "How to install mEGA-vIEW to your System"

@{b}@{u}INSTALLATION@{ub}@{uu}

As usual you should use the supplied Installer Script...however, here's
a short description how to install it manually:

@{b}1)@{ub} Copy mEGA-vIEW to a directory of your choice. Copy the mEGA-vIEW.cfg
   file to your FAME:ExternEnv/Doors/ drawer. Copy the supplied archiver
   to a directory where you've stored your archivers (normally C:).

@{b}2)@{ub} Start System-Editor, go to section Doors and add a new door with the 
   following settings:

    DoorCallName: V
       Door Path: <THE PATH WHERE THE mEGA-vIEW.FIM FILE IS LOCATED>
           Stack: Leave the default
       Door Type: FIM / Multinode
   Command Allow: NR AR CF RD SR

   Save these settings...that's it for FAME installation.

@{b}3)@{ub} Start now your Editor and load in the mEGA-vIEW.cfg file and adjust all
   Pathes and other values to your needs (The Preferences file contains also
   all descriptions for all configuration values).

@{b}4)@{ub} If you wish copy the supplied mEGA-vIEW_ext.cfg to FAME:externenv/doors/
   and enhance/change it to met your requirements. However this file is not
   required for mEGA-vIEW to work.

@{b}5)@{ub} Go into the BBS and type 'V' and the command prompt, you may then view 
   files ;)))

@endnode

@node "USAGE" "Configuration and usage of mEGA-vIEW"

@{b}@{u}CONFIGURATION@{ub}@{uu}

Well the main configuration is stored as @{fg shine}FAME:ExternEnv/doors/mEGA-vIEW.cfg@{fg text}.
All possible options are described in this file. All entries are using the
standard ReadArgs() format, which is @{fg shine}<PARAMETER> = <VALUE>@{fg text}. 

For detailed informations please look in the configfile or click @{"HERE" LINK SAMPLE_CONFIG} to see
an example configuration.

For external filetype support there exists a second configfile called
@{fg shine}FAME:ExternEnv/Doors/mEGA-vIEW_Ext.cfg@{fg text}. This Textfile has no description or
other text except the configuration data inserted. Detailed informations about
this configuration could be found in the @{"External FileTypes" LINK EXTERN} chapter.


@{b}@{u}USAGE@{ub}@{uu}

The usage of mEGA-vIEW is exactly the same like the internal viewer of FAME.
It supports all commands and has also some additional features, which are 
described here:

@{b}1)@{ub} Without arguments mEGA-vIEW starts and prompts you for the filename to view.
   You may now give the filename or a pattern and mEGA-vIEW will show the file
   if it exists. You may also add the keyword '@{b}NS@{ub}' after the pathname/filename
   to indicate that you wish to view the selected file NonStop (no pausing).
   Useful to view ANSI Animations....

@{b}2)@{ub} Start mEGA-vIEW with all parameters you require, i.e.:

                             '@{fg shine}v trsi*.txt NS@{fg text}'

   Will look in your current dirs for all files matching TRSI*.TXT and prompts
   you for every file.

@{b}3)@{ub} Start mEGA-vIEW with parameter '@{b}$@{ub}' to view Version and Compile Informations.

@{b}4)@{ub} Start mEGA-vIEW with parameter '@{b}NOASL@{ub}' to disable ASL
   support on local connects

I don't think that further informations are required, because mEGA-vIEW is 
programmed to give itself all infos to the user including very clear error
messages, so you shouldn't have any problems with it...
@endnode

@node "EXTERN" "Infos about the External Filetype support"

@{b}@{u}EXTERNAL FILETYPE SUPPORT@{ub}@{uu}

mEGA-vIEW introduces now a way to extend the functionality by supporting 
external programs for specific fileextensions. All you have to do is creating
a textfile containing the extension and the according command line, that's all.
I've decided to put this configuration into a seperate file to avoid overloaded
configfiles. All external Filetypes have to be entered in the file:

                  @{fg shine}FAME:ExternEnv/Doors/mEGA-vIEW_Ext.cfg@{fg text}

This file contains @{b}*ONLY*@{ub} configuration data, I don't want to built or adapt
another parser. The format is simple but it is important that you write down
the parameters exactly as described here.

@{u}An Example:@{uu}

@{b}----[CUT STARTS]----@{ub}

GIF   C:VT >%O %F INFO
JPG   C:FJPEG >%O %F INFO TEST

@{b}----[CUT ENDS]----@{ub}

^^^   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
|             +-> Command to execute
|-> Extension

First you have to enter the extension of the filetype you wish to support.
Next the command line has to be specified. You should enter here exactly
the same line you will enter also in a shell window to use that command.

The extension and the commandline must have at least one space between them!

mEGA-vIEW has to insert two things into your commandline, because of that
I've used two special '@{b}%@{ub}' codes to determine the position where the information
should be inserted. Currently these two codes are supported:

@{b}%O -@{ub} Defines mEGA-vIEW's redirection file. Just enter it at the position where
     the command requires the output parameter. For standard cli programs it
     should be always PRGNAME >%O PARAMETERS. It is important that YOU (!) set
     first the redirection char '@{b}>@{ub}' and write the @{b}%O@{ub} DIRECTLY after that sign!
     This is required to let the external program show it's output in the BBS.

@{b}%F -@{ub} This will be replaced by the full path and filename of the selected file.

Just repeat now all Extensions for which you want to have support.

To make things clear: This external configuration file is not required for
mEGA-vIEW to work! It's just an addition to allow further infos gained from
unknown files. If you feel okay with the direct support of mEGA-vIEW, just
forget this external support and enjoy mEGA-vIEW! ;)
@endnode

@node "TODO" "TO-DO List for mEGA-vIEW V3.4"

@{b}@{u}TODO@{ub}@{uu}

Some parts are currently not implemented because I want to test out first
the core of mEGA-vIEW before enhancing it with additional features. So please
all you Beta-Testers out there, TEST THIS THING AND REPORT BUGS TO ME! You
will find my e-mail adress when starting mEGA-vIEW with the '$' option. 

The following additional features are currently planned:

 - Global Viewing...well the code is already finished, but FAME has currently
   no support for this flag integrated (Door Commands), these functions for FAME
   are under development and will be soon ready for usage.

 - Support for V1.04 of the Amiga ARJ Porting, which allows to extract single
   files like LHA,LZX or ZIP..you will get a cursor controlled ARJ Window in 
   the next update when I have tested out V1.04 of the ARJ porting...

 - Support for UnACE...but I have currently no .ace archives here, if you have
   some, please send them to me (but not more than 200kb !!!)

 - Maybe PowerPacker support (like my MUI mEGA-vIEW has)

 - Maybe User configuration...but I have really no clue what the user should
   configure ;) If you have any ideas report them to me please...

 - An external configuration program for mEGA-vIEW is already under 
   development allowing the sysop to easily configure the door. This program
   will be MUI driven...


If you have any additional ideas or other suggestions for this or any other
of my programs feel free to contact me in my BBS or via e-mail to 
siegel@siegel.in-berlin.de. Have fun...
@endnode

